msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&policykit-kde; is a implementation of PolicyKit tool to the look and feel of "
"KDE."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"PolicyKit allows easy and secure password management, it can be used by "
"applications to ask their users for a password. Each application defines a set "
"of actions that can be executed by their program. The application will call "
"PolicyKit to see if the user can perform a given action, if not, the "
"application can issue the auth dialog where the user can enter his/her "
"password, root password, the password of a given group of users or even swipe "
"the finger."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:15
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&policykit-kde; consists of two applications: The Authorization agent that "
"receives requests for authentication, and shows a dialog asking for a password. "
"The Authorization manager that is used to manage the authorizations, it is "
"mainly used by system administrators that may want to change the default "
"behavior of a program policies."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For Qt/KDE developers there is Qt library to allow easy integration with you "
"application and PolicyKit."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: introduction.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For more information of how PolicyKit works, it's design and API visit <ulink "
"url=\"http://hal.freedesktop.org/docs/PolicyKit/\">PolicyKit Library Reference "
"Manual</ulink>"
msgstr ""
